Package: gginlay
Title: Add Inlays on a ggplot Interactively
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Mihai", "Valcu", , "Mihai.Valcu@bi.mpg.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6907-7802"))
Description: By using a shiny interface, this mini package lets you positioning insets (e.g. images or other inlays) exactly where you want them on a ggplot. To be more specific, this package generates the exact coordinates required by the patchwork::inset_element() function for the placement of the inset.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.0),
    ggplot2
Imports:
    methods,
    patchwork,
    shiny,
    shinyWidgets,
    gridlayout,
    bslib
Sugests:
    devtools, 
    jpeg, 
    png
Remotes:
    rstudio/gridlayout
